    "name": "Fraser Residence Nankai Osaka",
    "detail": "Before go, we check this hotel is ranked No.1 in Osaka hotels in tripadvisor with relative cheap price. We booked in agoda. During the checkin, the hotel staff recommend us to add another 3000yen to promote from 18m2 apt to a 44m2 apt. We accepted. Overall we stayed 5 hotels in japanese trip, this hotel is absolutely the best. Including the price, the staff, the service, the room and the location,everything. From Nankai namba station which is just across the road, it is easy to reach the kansai airport. With 5 min walking distance, it is easy to reach underground namba station. We bought a kansai two days pass in hotel frontdesk and use it to visit nara, kyoto, kobe and Arima Onsen hot spring.Absolutedly perfect! My wife asked for two bottles of water, the staff said OK via the phone and send to our room after 3 min and explained in fact, the bottle water was not included in the service. But since we don't know, they still send us as a service. Very friendly indeed!",
